{{Infobox person | pre-nominals = | name = William C. Schneider | post-nominals = | image = <!-- filename only, no "File:" or "Image:" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] --> | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1923|12|24}} | birth_place = New York, New York | baptised = <!-- will not display if birth_date is entered --> | death_date = {{death date and age|1999|12|24|1923|12|24}} | death_place = | death_cause = | body_discovered = | resting_place = [[Arlington National Cemetery]] | resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} --> | burial_place = <!-- may be used instead of resting_place and resting_place_coordinates (displays "Burial place" as label) --> | burial_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} --> | monuments = | residence = | nationality = | citizenship = | education = [[Catholic University of America]] | occupation = [[Aerospace engineer]] | years_active = | era = | employer = [[NASA]] | organization = | known_for = | notable_works = <!-- produces label "Notable work"; may be overridden by |credits=, which produces label "Notable credit(s)"; or by |works=, which produces label "Works"; or by |label_name=, which produces label "Label(s)" --> | style = | home_town = | spouse = <!-- Use article title or common name --> | partner = <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) --> | children = | parents = <!-- overrides mother and father parameters --> | mother = <!-- may be used (optionally with father parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays "Parent(s)" as label) --> | father = <!-- may be used (optionally with mother parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays "Parent(s)" as label) --> | relatives = | family = | callsign = | awards = }} '''William Charles Schneider''' ({{Birth date|1923|12|24}}{{mdash}}{{death date|1999|12|24}}) served in the [[United States Navy Reserve]] 1942-1946 as an Aviation Machinists Mate, 1st Class Petty Officer. He joined [[NASA]] in June 1963 and served as the [[Gemini program|Gemini]] mission director for seven of the ten piloted Gemini missions. From 1967 to 1968, he served as [[Apollo program|Apollo]] mission director and the Apollo program’s deputy director for missions. He then served from 1968 to 1974 as the [[Skylab program|Skylab]] program’s director. From 1974 to 1978, he worked as the Deputy Associate Administrator for [[Space Shuttle program|Space Transportation Systems]]. From 1978 to 1980, he served as the Associate Administrator for [[Spaceflight Tracking and Data Network|Space Tracking and Data]] systems. He received a Ph.D. in engineering from [[Catholic University of America]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/1160066/william-charles-schneider |title=William Charles Schneider (1923-1999) |website=www.findagrave.com |access-date=2018-07-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://history.nasa.gov/bioso-s.html |title=Biographies of Aerospace Officials and Policymakers, O-S |website=history.nasa.gov |access-date=2018-07-23}}</ref><ref name="USNM">{{Cite web |url=http://navylog.navymemorial.org/node/1677551 |title=Schneider, William |website=navylog.navymemorial.org |language=en |access-date=2018-07-23}}</ref>
== Awards == Schneider received the [[NASA Distinguished Service Medal]], NASA's highest award, in 1969.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://history.nasa.gov/SP-4012/vol4/appa.htm |title=SP-4012 NASA Historical Data Book: Volume IV NASA Resources 1969-1978 |work=history.nasa.gov |publisher=NASA |year=1993 |pages=Appendix A: NASA Honor Awards |access-date=2018-07-24}}</ref>
[[File:Jsc2011e075769 orig.jpg|thumb|Vice President Gerald R. Ford presented the Collier Trophy Award to Schneider in Washington.]] [[Gerald R. Ford]] presented the 1973 [[Collier Trophy]] to Skylab, with special recognition to Schneider and the three crews, "For proving beyond question the value of man in future explorations of space and the production of data of benefit to all the people on Earth."<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://naa.aero/awards/awards-and-trophies/collier-trophy/collier-1970-1979-winners |title=Collier 1970-1979 Recipients |website=naa.aero |publisher=National Aeronautic Association |language=en-US |access-date=2018-07-23}}</ref>
[[National Space Club]] awarded Dr. Schneider the 1974 award in aeronautical engineering.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1974/03/08/99160080.html?pageNumber=40 |title=National Space Club Issues 1974 Awards |date=1974-03-08 |work=New York Times |access-date=2018-07-23 |page=40 |language=en}}</ref>
The [[American Astronautical Society]] presented Schneider the 1974 [[Space Flight Award]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://astronautical.org/awards/space-flight/ |title=Space Flight Award |website=American Astronautical Society |language=en-US |access-date=2018-07-24}}</ref>
